
    WHAT was meant to be a dream holiday for an Australian
woman celebrating her 30th birthday turned into a nightmare after an
accident resulted in her leg being cut off.According to Coconuts,
Stacey Liddle from Brisbane was riding a motorbike she’d rented in the southern
Thai town of Phuket on 26 October. A passing tour bus smashed into her,
knocking her to the road. The bus then drove over her leg, crushing it.Stacey was rushed to Vachira Hospital where several
operations were performed to try and fix the severely broken leg. At this stage
