Stacey became infected with a superbug.A superbug is a strain of bacteria that has become
resistant to antibiotics, making it extremely life threatening. Fearing the
worst, Stacey was flown to Sydney in Australia in a special plane.Surgeons at Sydney’s Royal Prince Alfred Hospital had no
choice but to cut off her leg from the thigh down to save her life.But Stacey is amazingly upbeat about her situation.
According to the report, she said: “I have no regrets in the decision I made to
have it amputated. I felt quite unwell before the surgery. I got a superbug.“I am so grateful to be alive actually. I can see good
things coming out of this.“I want to use my incident and hopefully help others,
perhaps finish my counselling course and become a trauma counsellor.” Doctors are optimistic that the determined young woman
will be walking with the help of a false leg by June. 
